      "content": "To distinguish between stagnant stock and normal seasonal cycles, look at the \"days sales of inventory\" metric compared to your specific season's historical average. If a sweater pile is growing in the back room right now during summer, that's likely a seasonal mismatch rather than just slow turnover. You should also categorize your items by category and compare their movement rates; if one category is moving while others are stuck in the same season, the issue is likely specific to those styles. Finally, try to visually inspect the back room for items that have been there longer than a month without a price adjustment or promotion, as these are likely the red flags your business needs to address immediately.",
